From: "H. Peter Anvin" <hpa@zytor.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Oct 2018 09:19:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] termios, tty/tty_baudrate.c: fix buffer overrun
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.19.3
Git-commit: 991a25194097006ec1e0d2e0814ff920e59e3465

commit 991a25194097006ec1e0d2e0814ff920e59e3465 upstream.

On architectures with CBAUDEX == 0 (Alpha and PowerPC), the code in tty_baudrate.c does
not do any limit checking on the tty_baudrate[] array, and in fact a
buffer overrun is possible on both architectures. Add a limit check to
prevent that situation.

This will be followed by a much bigger cleanup/simplification patch.

